Day. The traditional practice of favouring Christianity is being systematically removed in Canada. Christian prayer is no longer mandatory in public schools and nativity scenes are no longer permitted in public schools (or any public property). &quot;Christmas&quot; is commonly renamed either Winter Holiday or WinterFest. It's time to also rename Easter. SpringFest would be appropriate. These holidays didn't originate with the Christians but were stolen from the Pagans. It's time to give them back to the Pagans. &#10;All holidays should be secular. Christian special days should no more be national holidays than should Jewish, Muslim, Sikh, or Pastafarian special days. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="966" language="en" documentId="1273" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Dennis Brady" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/tempers-flare-over-prayer-in-schools-1.1104775" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1273" notes="" title="Tempers flare over prayer in schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="166"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="167" end="811"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="812" end="966"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47"/></xmi:XMI>